data.title: Great food
data.text: This place is Awesome.  Amazing sandwiches, pizza, and chicken. The owner is great, sometimes he gives us free samples of food to go with our order

data.title: Ok, but nothing to sing about
data.text:
First, I ordered online around 10:40am and asked for my veal cutlut parm to be ready at 12:20pm. Apparently they didn't realize that and made my sandwich super early and called to make sure I was coming to pick it up because they said I had ordered it so long ago. That said, the guy in the restaurant was really nice.

Maybe if the sandwich had been fresh, it would have been better. As it was, it was warm enough and ok. I might go back and try something else, but I'll have to make a point of the time I plan to pick it up.

data.title: Food is not as good as it used to be
data.text:
Haven't been to Catalina's Pizza in quite some time, but thought I would try it out again.  Got Chicken Parm sub and it was horrible.  Took 2 bites and had to throw the rest away.  The chicken was very poor quality and I didn't like the sauce.  Also got a side of meatballs and they were not very good either.  Same sauce, which I didn't like and the meat just seemed to be low quality with more filler than beef.

I did like the french fries, they were cooked well and had a good taste.

Overall, I will not go back to Catalina's Pizza, there are too many other better places around.

data.title: New Owner
data.text:
A new owner has taken over at Catalina.   His pizza remains very good and has made some nice additions to the menu.   I was recently here and had the lasagna and bolgnaise sauce.   The bolaonaise sauce was very good with pasta.   I certainly would rate it up with the better Italian restaurants in the area!   

Is mostly take out but there are some seats available to eat in.   Nice friendly place!   I'll be back!
